114: | §6  Dual-format | `execution-protocol/06-dual-format.md` |\n115: | §7  REPAIR / §7.3 REBUILD | `execution-protocol/07-repair-mode.md` |\n116: | §8  Deviations | `execution-protocol/08-deviations.md` |\n117: | §9  Non-interactive | `execution-protocol/09-non-interactive.md` |\n118: | §10 Section generation | `execution-protocol/10-section-generation.md` |\n119: | §10.5 Tool discipline | inline below (universal) |\n120: | §11 Output sidecar | inline below (universal) |\n121: | §12 Delegated exploration | `execution-protocol/12-delegated-exploration.md` |\n122: | §13 Code-location | `execution-protocol/13-code-location.md` |\n123: | §14 Parallel fan-out | `execution-protocol/14-parallel-fanout.md` |\n124: \n125: A skill's route (e.g. `§2 → §10 → §10.5 → §11`) resolves each §N via this table:\n126: universal sections are already here; the rest are one file-read away. Existing\n127: \"see execution-protocol.md §N\" citations in the 123 skills keep working through\n128: this one redirect hop — no skill edits required.\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## 2. _progress.json — Early Signal Write\n133: \n134: **Purpose:** Prevents the orchestrator coordinator from sending SIGINT to a running skill.\n135: \n136: Write this as the **FIRST file action** in any skill execution (before creating any other outputs):\n137: \n138: ```json\n139: {\n140:   \"skill\": \"{skill-name}\",\n141:   \"session_id\": \"{SESSION_ID}\",\n142:   \"status\": \"RUNNING\",\n143:   \"started_at\": \"{ISO timestamp}\",\n144:   \"completed_at\": null,\n145:   \"total\": 0,\n146:   \"completed\": 0,\n147:   \"items\": []\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: Write to: `{output_folder}/_progress.json`\n152: \n153: **Update cadence:**\n154: - On FIC trigger (Section 5): `\"status\": \"COMPACTION_NEEDED\"`\n155: - On completion: `\"status\": \"COMPLETED\"`, `\"completed_at\": \"{ISO timestamp}\"`\n156: - On failure: `\"status\": \"FAILED\"`, `\"completed_at\": \"{ISO timestamp}\"`\n157: \n158: **Schema variants.** A skill picks ONE shape based on its work model. The common\n159: envelope (`skill`, `session_id`, `status`, `started_at`, `completed_at`) is identical"}}
