nt code already fixes this by:\n1. Navigating directly to `/auth/login`\n2. networkidle wait\n3. body click\n4. 45s timeout\n\nBut TC-83240 still fails with \"TC-83240 - ... Log in with test user credentials\" error. Looking at the error context more carefully, the error is at line 28 in LoginPage.ts which says `timeout: 15_000`. But current file has `timeout: 45_000` at line 45. This means the error is from a PREVIOUS run before the fix was applied.\n\nThe task says \"FIx this issues\" - the additional instructions show the error output and asks to fix those specific failing tests.\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Check if the current code actually already addresses these (may have been partially patched already)\n2. Identify what's still broken or not yet properly fixed\n3. Apply the remaining fixes\n\nLet me use MCP to inspect the live site to validate selectors for the newsletter input and the \"set your store\" link, since those might have different DOM structure.\n\nActually let me re-read the error carefully:\n- Error 2: `input[name=\"email\"][type=\"email\"]` at `LoginPage.ts:28` with 15000ms timeout\n- Current LoginPage.ts line 28: `await this.emailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });`\n  - Wait, no. Current line 45 has 45_000. Let me recount...\n\nLooking at current LoginPage.ts:\n```\nLine 28: // Using a 45s timeout for the email input because the UAT origin can be slow\nLine 32: async login(email: string, password: string): Promise<void> {\n...\nLine 45: await this.emailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 45_000 });\n```\n\nThe error says line 28. But in current code line 28 is a comment. This confirms the error is from old code that had `timeout: 15_000` at line 28. The current code is already patched.\n\nBut the task says to fix these issues, and these are the latest test results. So maybe even the patched code doesn't work, OR the task is giving me old errors and I need to verify.\n\nMost likely scenario: The current code in the repo (M = modified) is the partial fix, but either:\n1. The fixes aren't quite right (wrong selectors still), OR\n2. The task wants me to verify and ensure they're fixed\n\nGiven the additional instructions say \"Fix this issues\" with the specific errors, I should:\n1. Use MCP to inspect live UAT selectors for newsletter section and \"set your store\" link\n2. Check if login page selector is correct\n3. Apply any remaining fixes\n\nLet me use Playwright MCP to visit the live site and check.\n"}}
