{"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "The search page shows \"Nothing found!\" - this is interesting. The vitamins search returns no results on the UAT. This explains the TC-83238 and TC-83240 failures - when navigateToVitaminsPdp is called, `searchResultsPage.firstProductLink` won't be found because there are no product links (the search returns nothing).\n\nWait - but TC-83238 passed for Chromium. Only Firefox and WebKit fail with the \"Set Your Store\" timeout. So the navigation to the PDP works for Chromium - maybe the search DOES return results in Chromium headful but not in headless/FF/WebKit?\n\nActually, looking at the errors more carefully:\n- TC-83238 Firefox: \"waiting for locator('p.cursor-pointer.text-primary').filter({ hasText: /set your store/i }).first() to be visible\" at `openStoreSelectorDialog` - this happens AFTER the navigation to PDP succeeded (since the error is about the store selector, not about navigation)\n- TC-83238 WebKit: same error\n\nAnd for TC-83240 (Chromium + Edge):\n- Error: \"waiting for locator('input[name=\\\"email\\\"][type=\\\"email\\\"]').first() to be visible\" at LoginPage.ts:28\n- This is the OLD code (timeout 15s at line 28). The current code has 45s at line 45.\n- The error is from before the code was patched.\n\nSo the current code in the repo is already patched for TC-83240. The task is asking to fix these based on the PREVIOUS run's failures, and the code has been partially updated but maybe not enough.\n\nBUT the errors shown include \"6 failed\" in the CURRENT run. So either:\n1. The current code (which I see now) is what's running and still failing, OR\n2. The current code was fixed AFTER that run and WILL fix the issues\n\nLooking at LoginPage.ts again:\n- Line 28: `await this.emailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });`\nWait, let me re-read: the error at line 28 in the error log. Current code at line 28 is a comment. But the error says line 28. This could mean:\n1. The current code IS what was running (but line numbers shifted because code changed)\n2. OR the code was different when the test ran\n\nThe git status shows pages/LoginPage.ts is Modified (M). So yes, the code was changed AFTER the test run that showed these failures.\n\nGiven this, the task is: \"Fix these issues\" - and I should check what's CURRENTLY in the code and determine if additional fixes are needed.\n\nCurrently for TC-83240 (login):\n- LoginPage.ts navigates to `/auth/login` with 45s timeout - ALREADY FIXED in current code\n- BUT the failing error was at LoginPage.ts:28 with 15s. Current line 28 is a comment about 45s timeout. This is clearly already fixed.\n\nFor TC-83232 (newsletter):\n- home-page.spec.ts already has extensive retry logic with 45s final timeout\n- But the test still failed at the OLD line 414 (now 452) with timeout 30s\n- Current code has 45s at line 452: `await homePage.newsletterEmailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 45_000 });`\n- The selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` IS valid on the live site\n\nFor TC-83238 (store selector - Firefox/WebKit):\n- ProductDetailPage.ts already has a fallback mechanism (try \"Set your store\" for 5s, then fall back to \"Check availability\")\n- But the error was at line 262 with timeout 15000ms (old code). Current code has try/catch with 5s.\n\nSo: the current code changes (M) appear to already address these issues. But the task says \"Fix this issues\" based on the current error output. This suggests either:\n1. The fixes in M are incomplete/wrong, OR\n2. There are NEW issues I need to fix\n\nThe best approach: verify the current fixes are correct and make them MORE robust. Let me also look at error-context files for clues.\n\nAlso I notice from the search page: \"Nothing found!\" - this means the vitamins search is returning no results. This would cause TC-83238 and TC-83240 to fail at the PDP navigation step, not at the store selector step. But the error says they fail AFTER navigation to PDP (at the store selector). So something is different.\n\nWait - maybe the search DOES work when the page is loaded properly (e.g., when Chromium test runs, the search API returns results but on Firefox/WebKit with different headers it doesn't? Or the timing is different?)\n\nActually the most likely explanation: our MCP browser visited the search page and the UAT API returned \"Nothing found!\" at that moment. But during actual test runs, the search returns results. The UAT might be intermittently available.\n\nLet me focus on fixing what can be fixed:\n1. TC-83232: The selector is fine. The issue is the page scroll strategy. Need more robust scrolling.\n2. TC-83238 (FF/WebKit): The `p.cursor-pointer.text-primary` selector might be wrong for Firefox/WebKit where the page renders differently. Need to check.\n3. TC-83240 (Chromium/Edge): Login page - already fixed in current code.\n\nLet me navigate to a PDP to check the store selector DOM.\n"}}
