viewport. So `y=705.5` below the fold still counts as \"visible\".\n\nLet me reconsider. The `setYourStoreRect.top = 705.5` and `viewportHeight = 720`. This means the element IS just barely within the viewport. In headless Firefox/WebKit with a SMALLER viewport (e.g. 1280x720 or different), the element might be just outside the viewport.\n\nBut Playwright's `waitFor('visible')` shouldn't care about viewport position. It only cares about CSS visibility properties.\n\nHmm, let me look at the failing error again:\n```\nError: waiting for locator('p.cursor-pointer.text-primary').filter({ hasText: /set your store/i }).first() to be visible\nTimeout 15000ms exceeded at ProductDetailPage.ts:262\n```\n\nThis was the OLD code with 15s timeout. The CURRENT code has:\n1. try: `setYourStoreLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 5_000 })`\n2. catch: try `checkAvailabilityLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 })`\n\nIf the element exists in DOM and is CSS-visible, it should be found. Unless it's truly not mounted yet when Firefox/WebKit runs.\n\nThe root cause in Firefox/WebKit might be:\n1. Slower hydration means the \"Set your store\" paragraph doesn't render until after 5s + 15s = 20s\n2. OR the `p.cursor-pointer.text-primary` actually has DIFFERENT classes in Firefox/WebKit (unlikely but possible)\n\nMost likely explanation: the product found via search in Firefox/WebKit tests is DIFFERENT from the one in Chromium, and that different product's fulfillment section renders differently.\n\nActually, let me check if the scroll `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` is causing issues. When `inStorePickupRadio` doesn't exist, the scroll fails silently. But then the `waitForTimeout(2500)` doesn't scroll to the fulfillment area. The \"Set your store\" link is at y=705.5 which is just at the bottom of the viewport. If we scroll the page for any reason, it might go off-screen.\n\nThe most robust fix for TC-83238:\n1. Replace the `inStorePickupRadio.scrollIntoViewIfNeeded()` with a direct scroll to the fulfillment section (using a more reliable locator like `[class*=\"Availability\"]` or just scrolling by a fixed amount)\n2. Increase the `setYourStoreLink.waitFor` timeout from 5s to 12s \n3. Make the selector more flexible: `p[class*=\"cursor-pointer\"][class*=\"text-primary\"]` instead of `p.cursor-pointer.text-primary`\n\nAlso, since `inStorePickupRadio` doesn't exist on this product but it's expected for TC-83238, maybe the test should be fixed to scroll to the availability section more reliably.\n\nActually the BEST fix: change `openStoreSelectorDialog` to:\n1. Try to scroll to the availability section using a broader selector\n2. Give more time for the section to mount (increase timeout from 5s to 15s)\n3. Use a more robust scroll strategy\n\nLet me also check: what happens if we scroll the `p.cursor-pointer.text-primary` into view?\n\nOK, here's my plan for fixes:\n\n**Fix 1: TC-83232 Newsletter (home-page.spec.ts + HomePage.ts)**\n- The selector is correct (`div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]`)\n- The issue is that the scroll strategy doesn't trigger Builder.io's IntersectionObserver\n- Fix: In the retry loop, do incremental scrolling (viewport-height steps) instead of jumping to `document.body.scrollHeight`\n- Also add `page.waitForFunction` as a fallback that polls for the element in DOM\n\n**Fix 2: TC-83238 Store selector (ProductDetailPage.ts)**\n- The `inStorePickupRadio` selector `input[aria-label=\"Product Ship to Store Pickup Fulfillment Type\"]` doesn't exist on many products\n- When it doesn't exist, `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` fails silently and the page is not scrolled to the fulfillment area\n- Fix: Use a more reliable element to scroll to (like the availability section or the \"Set your store\" link itself)\n- Increase the timeout from 5s to 12-15s for setYourStoreLink\n- Also try scrollIntoViewIfNeeded on setYourStoreLink directly\n\n**Fix 3: TC-83240 Login (already fixed in current code)**\n- No additional changes needed - the current LoginPage.ts already navigates to `/auth/login` with 45s timeout\n\nLet me now implement the fixes:\n"}}
