{"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/pages/ProductDetailPage.ts", "content": "257:     /**\n258:      * Opens the store selector dialog and waits for it to be visible.\n259:      *\n260:      * Two states are handled:\n261:      *   1. No store set yet  -- a \"Set your store\" link is visible.\n262:      *   2. Store already set -- the site (e.g. via geolocation on Firefox/WebKit)\n263:      *      pre-selects a store, replacing the \"Set your store\" link with\n264:      *      \"Check Availability at other stores\". Clicking that link also opens\n265:      *      the `dialog#store-selector` so the rest of the flow is identical.\n266:      *\n267:      * Scrolls to the fulfillment section first to ensure intersection-observer\n268:      * elements are mounted before waiting.\n269:      */\n270:     async openStoreSelectorDialog(): Promise<void> {\n271:         // Scroll the fulfillment area into view so lazy-rendered elements mount.\n272:         await this.inStorePickupRadio\n273:             .scrollIntoViewIfNeeded({ timeout: 10_000 })\n274:             .catch(() => undefined);\n275: \n276:         // Allow a moment for intersection-observer elements to mount after the\n277:         // scroll. Firefox and WebKit hydrate more slowly than Chromium, so use\n278:         // a 2.5 s wait to give the store-selector link time to appear.\n279:         await this.page.waitForTimeout(2_500);\n280: \n281:         const checkAvailabilityLink = this.page\n282:             .locator('p.cursor-pointer')\n283:             .filter({ hasText: /check availability at other stores/i })\n284:             .first();\n285: \n286:         // Try \"Set your store\" first (no store set). locator.isVisible() does NOT\n287:         // accept a timeout option -- it returns immediately. Use waitFor with a\n288:         // short timeout inside a try/catch so we genuinely wait up to 5 s before\n289:         // falling back to \"Check Availability at other stores\" (store already set).\n290:         let setStoreVisible = false;\n291:         try {\n292:             await this.setYourStoreLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 5_000 });\n293:             setStoreVisible = true;\n294:         } catch {\n295:             setStoreVisible = false;\n296:         }\n297: \n298:         if (setStoreVisible) {\n299:             await this.setYourStoreLink.click();\n300:         } else {\n301:             await checkAvailabilityLink.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15_000 });\n302:             await checkAvailabilityLink.click();\n303:         }\n304: \n305:         await this.storeSelectorDialog.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 10_000 });\n306:     }\n307: \n308:     /**\n309:      * Searches for stores by postal code/city in the store selector dialog\n310:      * and waits for search results to appear (first \"Set Store\" button visible).\n311:      *"}}
