All three failures addressed. Summary of changes:

---

**TC-83232 — Newsletter timeout (Chromium + Edge)** → `tests/home-page.spec.ts`
- **Root cause**: `window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight)` jumped to the bottom of a barely-loaded page (~285px tall) before Builder.io mounted the newsletter section. The IntersectionObserver for the newsletter placeholder never fired.
- **Fix**: Replaced the single-jump scroll with an **incremental viewport-height loop** (up to 20 passes, 800ms between each). This ensures every Builder.io section's IntersectionObserver fires as the viewport passes over it. Retained `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` + 45s final `waitFor` as belt-and-suspenders.

**TC-83238 — Set Your Store timeout (Firefox + WebKit)** → `pages/ProductDetailPage.ts`
- **Root cause**: `inStorePickupRadio` (`input[aria-label="Product Ship to Store Pickup Fulfillment Type"]`) does NOT exist on many products (Ship-to-Home-only items). When its `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` silently failed, the fulfillment section was never scrolled into view, so the "Set your store" link's IntersectionObserver never fired.
- **Fix**: Added a **two-step scroll fallback** — (1) try `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` on `setYourStoreLink` itself, (2) unconditional `window.scrollBy(0, 60% of scrollHeight)` to guarantee the fulfillment area enters the viewport. Increased the `setYourStoreLink.waitFor` timeout from **5s → 12s** to give Firefox/WebKit time to hydrate.

**TC-83240 — Login timeout (Chromium + Edge)** → `pages/LoginPage.ts` *(already fixed in current code)*
- The current code already navigates to `/auth/login` directly (skipping the `/myaccount` redirect) and uses a 45s timeout. No additional changes were needed.
